HEADWORD: Figuration
<hw>Fig`u*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>figuratio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of giving figure
or determinate form; determination to a certain form.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>Mixture of concords and
discords.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Figurative</ent>⟦br⟧
